description: Here are a few excerpts from President Xi Jinping of China’s speech to business leaders in Seattle on Tuesday night.
title: Xi Jinping on ‘House of Cards’ and Hemingway
title_page: Xi Jinping on ‘House of Cards’ and Hemingway - The New York Times
maintext:
A Shout-Out for Netflix
Mr. Xi name-checked “House of Cards,” the Netflix series in which Kevin Spacey plays a power-hungry politician, to say that there was no ulterior motive to the corruption crackdown he has pursued in China and that it was not aimed at taking down rivals.
“It has nothing to do with a power struggle,” he said. “In this case there is no ‘House of Cards.’ ”
